records.addlTxt:
Defendant Brannon E Boatman in court with attorney Kelsey Morin.  Melissa Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads guilty to count #1.  Court finds the defendant guilty of count #1.  Count #2 is dismissed and read in.  State makes recommendations.  Attorney Morin makes statements.  Defendant makes statements.  
The Court Orders the Following: Count #1.  
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
4 months Huber with STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.  
Term of Probation: 1 Year May be transferred to Milwaukee County
Conditions of Probation:
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
No Use or Possession of llegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
Inform agent of all prescriptions;
Disclose to any physician in writing your drug history/dependency signed by your physician and provide a copy to your Agent. 
Sign Medical Release for Agent;
Condition Time: 10 days Huber with NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS -  STAYED to be used at the Agents discretion
FINE:  $379.00  to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA Surcharge: $250.00 to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 
Felony warnings, immigration warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.  
Expunction is conditionally granted upon completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.  Defendant must Petition the Court in writing upon successful completion of the sentence.
